      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LILSTREPO (7) is hard to knock having added to a string of top-two finishes when working to the front before scoring by more than 7m last start at Mildura, her third success from her last four outings. Cops a wide draw but is racing well enough to overcome that. RONNIE THE HAMMER (4) has come from the back row in both starts since a spell and hasn't been far from the placegetters. Suited up to a distance where he has won two of three attempts and should be close to peak fitness third-up. Could strike returning to the front row. INTERPRETATION (6) made it three wins from her last four starts when she came from wide on the back line to score by close to 8m over a similar distance at Shepparton last week. Up in grade but she is going well enough to take that step. JACCKA CONNOR NZ (8) looks close to a win after missing narrowly in a higher-graded race at Melton last time and draws for a nice trail.",
